cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use this repository, please cite it. Kirill Kruglov is the author and
  maintainer; Claude (Anthropic) and Codex (OpenAI) are AI collaborators (see
  CONTRIBUTORS.md). This is a research trail, not a peer-reviewed publication.
title: "Ascesis: a research trail of honest bridges in AI alignment"
abstract: >-
  A research trail for AI-alignment thinking, organized as honest bridges between
  existing fields, with pre-registered toy experiments and explicit field ownership.
  The current direction tests whether an active, type-blind arbiter (a "feeder") can
  hold a population's equilibrium against an adversarial fraction that games observable
  signals under hard optimization (reward hacking / Goodhart), and locates the
  observation-horizon boundary R* below which no blind mechanism holds permanence.
